.TH sillybearconvert 1
.SH NAME
sillybearconvert \- convert between Sillybear and OpenSSH private key formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sillybearconvert
.I input_type
.I output_type
.I input_file
.I output_file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Sillybear
and
.B OpenSSH
SSH implementations have different private key formats.
.B sillybearconvert
can convert between the two.
.P
Sillybear uses the same SSH public key format as OpenSSH, it can be extracted
from a private key by using
.B sillybearkey \-y
.P
Encrypted private keys are not supported, use ssh-keygen(1) to decrypt them
first.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I input_type
Either
.I sillybear
or
.I openssh
.TP
.I output_type
Either
.I sillybear
or
.I openssh
.TP
.I input_file
An existing Sillybear or OpenSSH private key file
.TP
.I output_file
The path to write the converted private key file. For client authentication ~/.ssh/id_sillybear is loaded by default
.SH SUPPORTED FORMATS
.B sillybearconvert
can read OpenSSH format files, and older PEM format files (
.B ssh-keygen
.I -m PEM
).
.B sillybearconvert
will write OpenSSH format files, usable with OpenSSH 6.5 and later.
Reading OpenSSH format DSS files or PKCS8 files is not currently supported.
.SH EXAMPLE
 # sillybearconvert openssh sillybear ~/.ssh/id_rsa ~/.ssh/id_sillybear
.SH AUTHOR
Matt Johnston (matt@ucc.asn.au).
.SH SEE ALSO
 sillybearkey(1), ssh-keygen(1)
.P
https://matt.ucc.asn.au/sillybear/sillybear.html
